INSERT INTO `courses` VALUES (33,1,'Ceramics A','ceramics-a','Explore the ceramicist in you','This course introduces students to different making processes, design and practical considerations. It gives students an opportunity to develop their own visual ideas and creative identity.','The course is designed for both beginners and students experienced in working with clay.','Week by week you will be taken through the various processes of ceramics and pottery beginning with the design process. After an initial introduction to the workshop and a health and safety demonstration, you will be taken through processes such as:\r\n\r\n– Coiling\r\n– Slab building\r\n– Pinching\r\n– Surface decoration\r\n– Screen printing\r\n– Raku firing\r\n\r\nYou can work on your own projects with guidance from the tutor. By the end of the course you will have a range of ceramic pieces of your own design.\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=43&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111027105007','',''),(34,1,'Art Workshop','art-workshop','','To develop your creativity further and improve existing skills through working from a life model or any subject matter of your own choice.  \r\n\r\n','Suitable for all levels of experience, as a broad range of skills are taught.','Working from the life model provided, still life set- ups,or own choice of subject matter, you will be encouraged to improve your existing skills and to develop your creativity further, in either 2D and 3D or both. \r\n\r\nThe course will cover the following topics: \r\n\r\nskills in draughtsmanship, line, tone, form and composition\r\nthe use of colour to create harmony and balance\r\nthe rhythms and movement in the composition\r\nthe use of a wide variety of 2D media, traditional and non traditional\r\nhow to build a 3D image in clay, wire, card\r\n\r\nStudents will be shown how to use less traditional media and materials such as collage, sticks, sponges etc. And will be encouraged to experiment and develop an individual style and approach to their work through group discussions and reference to relevant artists.\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=42&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111027104941','',''),(35,1,'Ceramics B','ceramics-b','','To introduce beginners to forming and surface marking techniques and support more experienced students with advice and ideas and encourage all to experiment and try new approaches.\r\n','Open to beginners with no prior experience','Week by week you will be introduced to the carrying elements of ceramics and pottery. After an initial introduction to different clays and the preparation of each type of clay, you will be taken through processes such as:\r\n– Slabs, coils, throwing and turning\r\n– Texturing, marking the clay surface and the use of coloured slips\r\n– Application of oxides\r\n– Application of under-glazes and glazes\r\n– Use of equipment such as slab roller, spray booth and extruder\r\n\r\nYou can work on your own projects. Guidance and tutorials are provided throughout the course. By the end of the course you will have a range of ceramic pieces from plant pots and vases to cups and saucers.\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=44&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111027105031','',''),(36,1,'Drawing and Painting A','drawing-and-painting-a','','Working from a life model, or still life if preferred, you will learn basic technical skills in drawing and painting and improve on your existing skills.  You will learn how to create interesting compositions in line, tone, and colour, experiment with new methods and media including 3D to develop an individual style and participate in group discussions on work done in class and by other artists.','Suitable for all levels of experience as a broad range\r\nof skills is taught.\r\n','Week by week, and through a step by step approach, you will be taught the basic skills of drawing and painting, which will cover areas such as:\r\n\r\n– How to draw accurately\r\n– How to use line\r\n– Introduction to tone and colour\r\n– Creating interesting compositions\r\n– Techniques of drawing using (but not limited to) pencil, charcoal &  pastel\r\n– Painting techniques especially acrylic.\r\n-  Modelling with clay, wire, card.\r\n\r\nIf you have previous experience you will be encouraged to improve your own existing skills and experiment with new methods and media.\r\n\r\nYou can also work on your own theme with help from the tutor. By the end of the course you will have a range of work in different\r\nmedia and an understanding of drawing and skills.\r\n','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativeshortcourses','course_image20111027105118','',''),(37,1,'Drawing and Painting B','drawing-and-painting-b','','You will learn to paint and draw from the figure.','Students of all abilities are welcome.','The week by week structure of the course introduces you to methods and techniques in drawing and painting with a particular emphasis on oil painting.\r\n\r\n– Tones (black & white as well as warm and cool colour tones)\r\n– Shapes and shadows\r\n– Working with restricted frames (rectangular, oval, circle and so forth)\r\n– Demonstrations on mixing paint\r\n\r\nA life model is provided and still-life is available if required. Guidance is provided by the tutor. You will end the course with a portfolio of work.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=56&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111027105147','',''),(38,1,'Kiln Formed Glass','kiln-formed-glass','','An introduction to processes and techniques associated with kiln-formed glass.\r\n\r\nStudents will learn and expand their kiln-formed glass skills while acquiring a better understanding of material, use of colour, texture and finishing techniques.','The course is designed for both beginners and intermediate students with some experience in working with kiln-formed glass.\r\n','You will be introduced to the processes of creating decorative pieces of glass using kiln-forming techniques. \r\n\r\nYou will have the opportunity to:\r\n\r\n– Learn how to cut glass\r\n– Use colouring agents such as metal oxides, enamels and frits\r\n– Learn the processes of slumping glass into or over a mould\r\n– Learn about the firing procedures and annealing cycles\r\n– How to use the sand blaster\r\n– Learn techniques for finishing\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course you will have a range of glassware pieces from decorative wall panels and small pendants to fruit bowls and coasters.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=48&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111027105215','',''),(39,1,'Printmaking A','printmaking-a','','To introduce and develop printmaking skills as part of a fine art activity.\r\n','The activity can be geared to suit your interests and experience, from complete beginners to advanced study.\r\n','The course will allow you to uncover printmaking methods and techniques. With practical, hands on experience some of the aspects you will cover include:\r\n\r\n– Simple methods of printmaking such as collographs\r\n– Etching\r\n– Relief printing (wood and linocut)\r\n– Painting processes – monoprinting & monotyping\r\n– Using flat plate and the application of ink\r\n\r\nYou will have the opportunity to focus on one or two methods for your own projects if you wish. By the end of the course you will have an understanding of print processes and a portfolio of work.\r\n\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=49&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111027105439','',''),(40,1,'Printmaking B','printmaking-b','','To develop existing printmaking skills or to act as an introduction to a range of printmaking processes.\r\n','Ideal for beginners with little or no experience but also for those with some prior knowledge i.e. art teachers or fine artists.	\r\n','The course will allow you to uncover printmaking methods and techniques. With practical, hands on experience some of the areas you will cover on the course include:\r\n\r\n– Introduction to relief/intaglio print processes\r\n– A focus on collograph and monotyping\r\n– Introduction to silkscreen\r\n– Etching & linocutting\r\n\r\nYou will be encouraged to pursue your own ideas and projects with the support of the tutor. Learning will be through regular demonstrations.\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course you will have an understanding of printmaking processes and a selection of prints.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=50&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111027105547','',''),(41,1,'Sculpture','sculpture','','The aims of the course are to encourage students in the appreciation and acquisition of the traditional crafts and knowledge of the practice of sculpture in all its forms.\r\n','Suitable for beginners and those with more experience, as tutorials and demonstrations can act as an introduction or refresher.\r\n','The course introduces you to sculptural techniques using a range of materials and media. Taking inspiration from the life model you will be encouraged to work on your own ideas and develop your own style. \r\n\r\nThe course will cover areas such as:\r\n– Forming figures in a range of material including wire, plaster or clay\r\n– Demonstrations in armature building\r\n– Introductions to methods such as moulding, casting in wax, plaster and ciment fondu\r\n– Exploration of carving and constructing techniques and methods where the facilities of the department allow.\r\n\r\nYou will end the course with an understanding of sculptural techniques and a selection of sculptural pieces.\r\nThere are welding and forge facilities available within the workshop, however prior experience of using such facilities will need to be proven prior to use.\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=51&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111027105622','',''),(42,1,'Textiles','textiles','','To explore the properties of different materials and fabrics through various printing and colouration processes.\r\n','The class is suitable for both beginners and returning students.\r\n','Week by week you will be introduced to different screen printing processes through demonstrations from tutors. \r\n\r\nThe course will cover areas including:\r\n\r\n– Use of various print pastes and binders\r\n– Use of dyes (dependent on materials)\r\n– Colouration techniques\r\n– Print techniques\r\n– Stitch\r\n\r\nYou will be encouraged to experiment with techniques and processes that you have learned and will be given the opportunity to work on your own ideas and projects.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=52&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111027105702','',''),(43,2,'Fashion Design for Beginners','fashion-design-for-beginners','','– To gain knowledge of the fashion and textiles industries and to practise the essential skills necessary to create a fashion portfolio\r\n– To research trend themes and create inspirational\r\nstoryboards\r\n– To learn how to develop and use visual research\r\nto realise design ideas\r\n– To develop initial ideas into contemporary designs\r\nfor fashion garments and accessories.\r\n','The course is suitable for beginners or those with some background in fashion or textiles design. The course is ideal for learners wishing to progress from A-level to BA Hons/FdA Fashion courses.\r\n','A course ideal for beginners who wish to learn about the design processes for fashion. On the course you will:\r\n– Create a set of storyboards showing an overview\r\nof fashion design themes for the forward season\r\n– Learn to develop your awareness of current/\r\nseasonal trends\r\n– Develop your own individual design theme and\r\ncreate a storyboard with colour palette\r\n– Experiment with illustration techniques to present\r\nideas\r\n– Produce a design board for a capsule collection\r\nfollowing your own theme.\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course you will have a folder/sketchbook of visual research, a portfolio of designs and design boards.\r\n','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativeshortcourses','course_image20111027104559','',''),(44,2,'Jewellery','jewellery','','To teach basic bench skills needed to produce jewellery.\r\n','The course caters for all abilities','Through weekly tutorials and demonstrations you will learn the techniques and processes of silver jewellery making, initially working with copper and then moving onto silver.\r\n\r\nThe course will cover:\r\n\r\n– Learning the basic skills required, such as soldering, fuming & annealing\r\n– Creating designs from your own ideas\r\n– Working with silver in ring making\r\n– Learning how to create a cabochon stone setting\r\n– Polishing and finishing techniques\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course students will have a good understanding of the techniques used as well as finished pieces of jewellery.\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=47&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111027104654','',''),(45,2,'Illustration','illustration','','To provide a stimulating, enjoyable and supportive environment in which to develop the work of students and give an insight into the illustration industry.\r\n','All levels. Most typically previous participants have included art students and those who have drawn for pleasure and want to develop their skills.\r\n','Over the duration of the course you will be introduced to a new and challenging way to explore the different aspects of illustration. Week by week the course will consist of:\r\n– Introduction to a variety of illustrative styles\r\n– Observational drawing\r\n– Exploration of responding to word, ideas or short pieces of text\r\n– Short exercises\r\n– Working to a given brief or your own idea\r\n\r\n\r\nBy the end of course students will have an understanding of illustration as well as a portfolio of drawings and sketches.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=46&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111027104640','',''),(46,2,'Pattern Cutting for Beginners','pattern-cutting-for-beginners','','This course is suitable for those who want to develop or improve their knowledge of pattern cutting and making skills.','This course is perfect for those who have little or no experience of creating patterns for women’s clothing.\r\n','This 14 week course will teach you the skills needed to create your own clothes. Week by week the tutor will take you through areas such as:\r\n\r\n– Creating block shapes including a bodice and a skirt\r\n– Manipulating darts\r\n– Cutting garment components\r\n– Adapting blocks, for example adapting the skirt block to an A line skirt, circular, four gored and straight skirt\r\n– Basic construction processes\r\n\r\n\r\nYou will leave the course with a range of prototypes of clothes made from your own patterns as well as an understanding of the processes behind pattern cutting.\r\n','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativeshortcourses','course_image20111027104726','',''),(47,2,'Pattern Cutting for Intermediates','pattern-cutting-for-intermediates','','This course is designed to advance learners’ pattern-cutting skills. It will cover more advanced features of pattern manipulation and adaptation. Learners will produce a pattern from a design of their own choice.\r\n','This intermediate course is for those who have completed the Pattern-Cutting for Beginners course or who have some previous experience of pattern cutting. \r\n\r\nThis course would be suitable for those who aspire to make clothes to professional standards. This course is perfect for those who have little or no experience of creating patterns for women’s clothing.','On this course you will advance your skills in pattern cutting to include garments such as women’s trousers and dresses. \r\n\r\nOver the weeks you will:\r\n\r\n– Create a trouser block\r\n– Draft a pair of trousers with a waistband and pockets\r\n– Learn advanced techniques of pattern manipulation and adaptation.\r\n– Learn how to layout and cut fabric\r\n– Create a Princess Line dress with facings and features such as sleeves and collars.\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course you will have created a garment of your own design.\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=96&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222122944','',''),(48,2,'Pattern Cutting - Advanced','pattern-cutting-advanced','','At the end of the course you will produce a varied patterns from a design of your own choice.','Advanced students who have previously attended Pattern Cutting for Beginners and for Intermediates.\r\n','Succeeding Pattern Cutting for Beginners and for Intermediates, this advanced level course will allow you to develop your skills through further study of manipulation techniques and the creation of more complex patterns for all types of garments.\r\n\r\nUsing your own personalised blocks, you will:\r\n\r\n– Adapt your block to create other styles\r\n– Customise your block for an individual fit\r\n– Use advanced construction techniques\r\n– Design and create a garment\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course you will leave us with a personalised block, an accurate pattern of your own design and a fitted toile. You will also have a greater understanding of how to create different styles using basic blocks, which will enable further pattern development.\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=95&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111027104712','',''),(49,3,'MAYA: Fundamental Modelling','maya-fundamental-modelling','','The course will provide you with the fundamental skills required to create, texture, light and render 3D models/assets.','This course is aimed at beginners – an ideal follow-on from Maya: Fundamental Animation. ','The course will take you through the varying aspects of 3D modelling using 3D Maya software. There will be an initial introduction to\r\nthe software, the user interface and tools.\r\n\r\nWeek by week you will cover:\r\n\r\nCreating and modifying objects\r\n– Reference and image planes\r\n– Problem solving\r\n– Introduction to mapping concepts\r\n– Introduction to texturing\r\n– Work flows and other modelling methods\r\n– Lighting and cameras\r\n\r\nIn a short project you will be able to utilise the processes taught over the previous weeks. By the end of the course you will have a project folder that contains all the work created over the duration of the course that will include 3D files as well as 2D rendered imagery of your projects.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=41&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222123114','',''),(50,3,'MAYA: Fundamental Animation','maya-fundamental-animation','','The course will provide you with the fundamental skills required to animate and render 3D assets.','This course is aimed at beginners – an ideal follow-on from Maya: Fundamental Modelling\r\n','Over the ten weeks you will be introduced to 3D Maya software and the principles of animation. week by week you will be taken through topics such as:\r\n\r\n– Graph editor\r\n– Animation controllers\r\n– Workflows\r\n– Storyboard\r\n– Rendering\r\n– 3D Cameras\r\n\r\nThroughout the course you will work on your own projects. At the end of the course you will bring together all you have learned to create a short animation piece. You will have a project folder that contains all the work created over the duration of the course. This will include 3D files as well as 2D rendered imagery of your projects.\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=40&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222123024','',''),(51,3,'Digital Photography','digital-photography','','To enable students to gain an understanding of their cameras and be able to use them to create more effective imagery.\r\n','Anyone who would like to have a greater understanding of digital photography by considering the principles of digital image making and putting them into practice.\r\n','This course will introduce you to the digital camera (compact or DSLR) through its components and their functions. Over the weeks you will be covering topics such as:\r\n\r\n– Composition\r\n– Subject choices\r\n– Lighting\r\n– Introduction to image editing\r\n– Introduction to image management\r\n– Portraiture or still life photography\r\n– Location and studio based photography\r\n\r\nYou will be encouraged to explore experimental photography as well as develop your own projects and ideas. You will end the course with an understanding of the principles of digital photography and a portfolio of work.\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=54&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222123230','',''),(52,3,'Dreamweaver for Beginners','dreamweaver-for-beginners','','This course aims to provide an introduction to the creation of a commercial website.\r\n\r\n','No previous experience necessary. Ideal for graphic designers, teachers, artists and photographers.\r\n','This course will introduce you to building your website using Adobe Dreamweaver. There will be an initial introduction to the software, the interface and the tools. Week by week the course will cover:\r\n\r\n– HTML & XHTML\r\n– Hand-coding a website\r\n– Web structures on Dreamweaver\r\n– Introduction to Adobe Photoshop for the web\r\n– CSS styling & typography\r\n– Introduction to Adobe Flash for the web\r\n– Exploration of blogs, accessibility, forums and more\r\n\r\nThere will be a brief insight into the history and technology of the web. By the end of the course you will have your own website and the skills required to maintain the site.\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=62&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222123329','',''),(53,3,'Photography','photography','','To enable students to create exciting imagery using both digital and film based processes.\r\n','Keen photographers of all abilities.','The course will introduce you to the functions and features of film based and digital cameras. Working on a three week rotation from the studio/dark rooms/location the course will emphasise areas such as:\r\n\r\n– Lighting\r\n– Location photography\r\n– Studio photography\r\n– Darkrooms – Colour/Black & White\r\n– Converting digital to analogue & vice versa\r\n\r\nDemonstrations and tutorials will guide and encourage you to work on your own projects and ideas. There will be a location trip either as a photographic exercise or exhibition visit. By the end of the course you will come away with a portfolio of\r\nphotographic work.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=53&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222123506','',''),(54,3,'Photoshop for Beginners','photoshop-for-beginners','','The overall aim of this course is to provide students with the basic skills in editing and retouching images.\r\n','Beginners.  Would suit those wishing to learn basic image management.','After an initial introduction to the software, you are taken through processes such as:\r\n\r\n– Colour Print Management, Editing (Heal brush tool, Cropping)\r\n– Digital printing and scanning\r\n– Filters and basic retouching\r\n– Colour cast and adding colour into an image\r\n\r\nThe course will also touch on some basic areas of design to ensure you are able to use the skills you have learned to carry on producing quality images. You will be given the opportunity to get practical experience in using these skills in class by applying your knowledge to your own images.\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=61&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222123741','',''),(55,3,'Photoshop for Intermediates','photoshop-for-intermediates','','The overall aim of this course is to provide students with knowledge of Photoshop a a more in-depth look at the tools within this programme.','Following on from the basics, this course would suit students wishing to develop their post-production skills for personal or professional interest.','On this course you will further your knowledge of Adobe Photoshop software. Week by week you will be taken through the following elements of the programme:\r\n\r\n\r\n– Colour management/print management\r\n– Digital tablets use for editing\r\n– Advanced filters and retouching\r\n– Colour manipulation\r\n\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course you will have advanced your skills and knowledge of Photoshop and have a portfolio of work\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=97&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222123946','',''),(56,3,'WEB 2.0 for Beginners','web-20-for-beginners','','This course aims to provide an introduction to the creation of a commercial website.','This course is ideal for those who have some experience of using the internet but would like to develop their knowledge and utilise free resources.\r\n','An introductory course to the world wide web version 2.0. The course will look at a variety of applications and user friendly interfaces. Some of the programmes and applications you will look at on the course include, but are not limited to:\r\n– Google Applications such as Google Blogger\r\n– Online photo site with photo editing\r\n– Business tools\r\n– Online audio and video streaming\r\n– Social networks such as Twitter and Facebook\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course you will have the basic skills to manipulate photos, audio and video for the web. You will also be confident in creating blogs and making a personal site using ready-to-use online tools.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=64&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222124140','',''),(57,4,'Confidence in Computer Music Sequencing','confidence-in-computer-music-sequencing','','To provide Continuing Professional Development and support for school teachers and instrumental peripatetic tutors.\r\n','Anyone wishing to learn more about music technology and feel more confident in the technological environments of modern music classrooms.\r\n','An ideal course for music teachers of all levels. The course will provide a balance between theory and practical application of computer music sequencing. On the course you will:\r\n\r\n–	Develop sequencing techniques in Cubase, Logic and Reason. All concepts are demonstrated in each 	program in order to ensure that you can get the most out of your chosen sequencing package in your 	school\r\n– Integrating Audio, Midi and Sampling\r\n– Automating parameters\r\n– Editing techniques\r\n','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativeshortcourses','course_image20111027105121','',''),(58,4,'LOGIC for Beginners','logic-for-beginners','','This course is now called Making Music for Beginners','','','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=108&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111027105137','',''),(65,4,'Advanced Rhythmic Techniques - The Schillinger System','advanced-rhythmic-techniques-the-schillinger-system','','This topic is concerned with introducing principles of rhythmic theory and key techniques for the creation of the rhythmic components that will later grow into extended forms.\r\n\r\nCPD - 30 Credits','The course is aimed at music teachers and professionals wishing to gain a simple understanding of the Schillinger Compositional System.','Various sources will be drawn into this module but the Schillinger System of Musical Composition will provide the main focus. We will start by establishing the physical basis of music and making a direct connection with musical pulse, meter and rhythm.\r\n\r\nThe course will rapidly move on to discuss:\r\n\r\n–  representation of rhythm and duration\r\n–  pulse interference\r\n–  symmetrical and asymmetrical rhythmic patterns\r\n–  the creation of balanced, expanding and contracting phrases\r\n–  the family tree concept of subdivision, power series and involution –  growth series and coefficients of recurrence.','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativelearning','course_image20111027105104','',''),(66,7,'Changing Media Environments','changing-media-environments','','The module will help SME media businesses plan\r\nfor growth effectively. By understanding how\r\nmarket trends and changing technologies are\r\nshaping current and future media consumption,\r\nparticipants will be better equipped to take\r\nadvantage of technological innovation, emergent\r\nmarkets and new audiences. They will understand\r\nthe implications of growth and the need for new\r\nbusiness models and survival strategies.','These courses are part of the Build Your Own MA\r\nportfolio of Professional Media Short Courses being\r\ndelivered by participating Skillset Media Academies\r\nacross England.','At the end of the module participants will be able to:\r\n– Examine and understand potential growth\r\nstrategies including organic growth, mergers and\r\nacquisitions and franchising\r\n– Assess benefits in downsizing, retrenchment and\r\nconsolidation\r\n– Assess business models which would suit your\r\nown business\r\n– Identify strategic alliances, potential partners and\r\ncollaborators\r\n– Protect and make good use of intellectual\r\nproperty rights\r\n– Understand the changing market conditions of\r\ntheir business\r\n– Observe the three key stages of change that\r\npeople need to work through and accept\r\n– Identify the nature of incremental and\r\ntransformational changes\r\nSelf-managed independent study is supported\r\nby tutorials either face-to-face or through distant\r\nlearning media, which handle the process of\r\nenquiry, and','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativelearning','course_image20111027110039','',''),(67,7,'Managing Creativity','managing-creativity','','Sound project management, effective teamwork\r\nand adaptability to change are all essential\r\nelements in business success. But in the most\r\nsuccessful media enterprises these elements are\r\nfurther enhanced by clear and decisive leadership.\r\nSo what defines a good leader? How do leadership\r\nskills differ from those required to manage projects\r\nand staff? How can enhanced leadership skills\r\nimprove a creative business? The aim of this\r\nmodule is to increase participants’ contribution to\r\nthe achievement of their own business goals and\r\nobjectives.','These courses are part of the Build Your Own MA\r\nportfolio of Professional Media Short Courses being\r\ndelivered by participating Skillset Media Academies\r\nacross England.','This module will broaden the learner’s knowledge\r\nand understanding of creativity as an experience,\r\nas a process, as an important element in the\r\nMedia Industries, and how creative working can\r\nbe managed effectively. It will further develop the\r\nlearner’s experience of enquiry and communication\r\npractices and skills at a standard appropriate for\r\npostgraduate study.\r\nIt will also develop the learner’s abilities to locate,\r\nevaluate, organise and make use of information\r\nfrom diverse sources to present a coherent and\r\npersuasive argument or case. It will help them work\r\nin an autonomous way making good use of time\r\nand resources and showing initiative and personal\r\ndirection in enquiry and communication.','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativelearning','course_image20111027110359','',''),(68,7,'Managing Digital Content','managing-digital-content','','This course enables the learner to develop a clear\r\nunderstanding of key ideas, concepts and terms\r\nin the field of digital media and in contemporary\r\ndigital media technologies. It includes the effective\r\nmanagement of digital media assets and ideas\r\nabout databases, meta data, and the emerging\r\n‘universe of things’. The course has a primarily\r\ntechnical and application of technology focus. It\r\nlooks at the uses of file formats and codecs in the\r\nmedia industries generally and in the leaner’s own\r\nsector specifically.','These courses are part of the Build Your Own MA\r\nportfolio of Professional Media Short Courses being\r\ndelivered by participating Skillset Media Academies\r\nacross England.','This module will broaden the learner’s knowledge\r\nand understanding of creativity as an experience,\r\nas a process, as an important element in the\r\nMedia Industries, and how creative working can\r\nbe managed effectively. It will further develop the\r\nlearner’s experience of enquiry and communication\r\npractices and skills at a standard appropriate for\r\npostgraduate study.\r\nIt will also develop the learner’s abilities to locate,\r\nevaluate, organise and make use of information\r\nfrom diverse sources to present a coherent and\r\npersuasive argument or case. It will help them work\r\nin an autonomous way making good use of time\r\nand resources and showing initiative and personal\r\ndirection in enquiry and communication.','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativelearning','course_image20111027110634','',''),(69,7,'Managing Digital Imagery','managing-digital-imagery','','Digital imagery is a key element of today’s media\r\nindustries. This course will consider the knowledge\r\nand skills needed for preparing still and moving\r\nimage material for archiving, for web, television (SD\r\nand HD), small screen and mobile devices, print,\r\nand projection. It looks at media and file formats,\r\ncodecs, lossy/non-loss issues, colour models,\r\naspect ratio and screen resolution (size and pitch),\r\ncropping and aesthetics/meaning.','These courses are part of the Build Your Own MA\r\nportfolio of Professional Media Short Courses being\r\ndelivered by participating Skillset Media Academies\r\nacross England.','The course covers a wide range of ideas and\r\npractices involved in working effectively with\r\ndigital imagery. To undertake the course learners\r\nwill need personal or workplace access to digital\r\nmedia workstations and software packages for the\r\nmanipulation of pixel-based still images and for\r\ndigital video editing. Learning content will cover:\r\n– Pixel Image concepts – resolution, colour depth,\r\nfile format and compression/quality balance\r\n– Pixel Image handling tools – crop, resize with\r\nproportion control, colour format, colourise,\r\nenhance contrast, brightness, copy/ paste and\r\ncomposite, layers, flatten/ merge layers,\r\n– File handling – export/save for to appropriate\r\nformat, log metadata\r\n– Principles of digital video – digitisation and\r\ncapture from source, tape, disc and solid state\r\nmemory, line in and level controls, formats,\r\ncodecs, project files, rendered files, save, export,\r\n– Digital video processes – import, load, edit, start,\r\nend, mix effects, insert, title, mattes, render to\r\nsize, format, export, log, label, metadata','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativelearning','course_image20111027110925','',''),(70,7,'Managing Media Projects','managing-media-projects','','By critically examining the idea of a project and\r\nwhat it means this module develops the learner’s\r\ncritical awareness of what a project is and how it\r\ncan be understood and managed effectively.\r\nLearners will gain a broad perspective of project\r\nmanagement, identify the skills and planning tools\r\nrequired and design a basic project specification\r\nand overview plan, and look at a range of\r\ncontemporary approaches to project management.','These courses are part of the Build Your Own MA\r\nportfolio of Professional Media Short Courses being\r\ndelivered by participating Skillset Media Academies\r\nacross England.','During the course learners will carefully consider\r\ndifferent approaches to project planning and project\r\nmanagement, including such processes such\r\nas SCRUM, CRYSTAL and PRINCE2. Learners\r\ncompleting the course will have seen how to:\r\n– Identify risks, why projects fail and the\r\nimplications of failure\r\n– Have an overview of project management/\r\ndefinitions\r\n– Apply the project process cycle\r\n– Plan project specifications – methodologies,\r\nmechanics and tools, budgets\r\n– Be aware of the human aspects – teamwork,\r\nwith an opportunity for team exercises\r\n– Develop a project schedule and action plan','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativelearning','course_image20111027111117','',''),(71,7,'Market Opportunities in the Creative Industries','market-opportunities-in-the-creative-industries','','This module has two main elements; Mapping the\r\nCreative Industries and Intellectual Property and\r\nYour Business. Through these two elements leaners\r\nwill develop their knowledge of the broad economic\r\nrole of the Creative Industries and their own sector,\r\nand develop their understanding of the role of IPR\r\nin the creation and management of wealth in a\r\nmodern society.','These courses are part of the Build Your Own MA\r\nportfolio of Professional Media Short Courses being\r\ndelivered by participating Skillset Media Academies\r\nacross England.','This module aims to develop the learner’s\r\nknowledge of and thinking about some of the\r\ncurrent debates and discussions about the creative\r\nindustries and their role in international, national\r\nand regional contexts, including their role within a\r\nmodern economy. In addition, learners will develop\r\nan understanding of how Intellectual Property (IP)\r\nrelates to their business, which is essential if they\r\nwant to stay competitive and avoid real commercial\r\nrisks.','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativelearning','course_image20111027111413','',''),(72,7,'Media Culture & Theory','media-culture-and-theory','','This module enables the learner to develop a range\r\nof enquiry skills that support effective study and to\r\nevaluate a broad range of information sources and\r\ncritically appraise media artefacts. Learners will\r\nengage with the work of prominent media theorists\r\nand commentators and look at a diverse range of\r\nsources, to develop a deeper understanding of their\r\nown sector from a cultural perspective. Topics dealt\r\nwith include things such as semiotics, structuralism,\r\nthe work of Marshall McLuhan, cybernetics, memes,\r\nnarratology, ludology, transmediation, media\r\nconvergence and the emergence of a digital culture.','These courses are part of the Build Your Own MA\r\nportfolio of Professional Media Short Courses being\r\ndelivered by participating Skillset Media Academies\r\nacross England.','This is an enquiry led module where the learner\r\napplies a key media idea or theory to a range of\r\nartefacts they select, or to activities within their own\r\nindustry, company, practice. This includes:\r\n– Using print and on-line sources and strategies\r\nfor information handling literature such as\r\nliterature search approaches\r\n– Using a range of sources and evaluating the\r\nstanding of authors\r\n– Effective use of search engines\r\n– Note gathering and management\r\nLearners will develop their ability to discuss and\r\ncomment on media artefacts using current ideas\r\nand theories. This is an invaluable skill in the media\r\nindustries as it underpins market analysis and an\r\nability to evaluate future projects.','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativelearning','course_image20111027111637','',''),(73,7,'Media Strategies & Communications','media-strategies-and-communications','','This course is a unique combination of topics that\r\nenable Media professionals to develop business\r\nacumen, market awareness and innovative\r\napproaches. To be successful in the creative media\r\nindustries today, it is essential to have a strong\r\ngrounding in a number of areas including the art of\r\nnegotiation, an ability to define and understand the\r\nmarket, and to find increasingly innovative routes to\r\nthat market through social media.','These courses are part of the Build Your Own MA\r\nportfolio of Professional Media Short Courses being\r\ndelivered by participating Skillset Media Academies\r\nacross England.','The course is organised around three key topics:\r\nUnderstanding Your Market:\r\nThis section will introduce the kinds of market\r\nresearch used in the media industries and show\r\nhow it is a vital technique to both assess the\r\ncommercial viability of your business ideas and\r\nforecast sales.\r\nNegotiating and Influencing Skills:\r\nThe ability to negotiate and influence effectively\r\nis vital for creative businesses – setting up a deal\r\nor reaching an agreement can be tricky to pull off\r\nsuccessfully.\r\nMarketing through Social Networks:\r\nThis element of the course explores the current\r\nstate of play of social networks and shows how to\r\nbegin using social media and social / professional\r\nnetworks to find and build an audience.','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativelearning','course_image20111027111849','',''),(74,7,'ProjectManagement & the Project Life Cycle','projectmanagement-and-the-project-life-cycle','','Understanding the contexts in which a media\r\nenterprise project is placed is key to many aspects\r\nof its development, design, production and\r\nsuccess. The course will also further develop the\r\nlearner’s critical thinking about the project in the\r\nmedia enterprise and examine various methods for\r\nmanaging documentation.','These courses are part of the Build Your Own MA\r\nportfolio of Professional Media Short Courses being\r\ndelivered by participating Skillset Media Academies\r\nacross England.','Documentation of a media project ranges from\r\nthe logging of work done, to financial record\r\nkeeping, through continuity logs, and keeping\r\ntrack of variables used in media authoring.\r\nEffective documentation ensures effective project\r\ncompletion.\r\nThis module is about mapping the contexts of a\r\nwork-based project, for example:\r\n– market\r\n– audience\r\n– field\r\n– genre\r\n– company strategic view\r\n– company history\r\n– skills and expertise/knowledge base\r\n– developmental views (skills, knowledge updating,\r\nnew market, new product line)\r\nBased on a critical reflective evaluation of a\r\nwork-based project this module develops critical\r\nand evaluative thinking and a range of enquiry and\r\ncommunication skills.','http://go.herts.ac.uk/creativelearning','course_image20111027112104','',''),(75,3,'Motion 101:','motion-101','Introduction to Motion 4','123456','This class is designed for students who are looking to learn more about creating motion graphics using Motion and who prefer hands-on, interactive instruction.\r\n•  Understanding behavior-based animation and templates\r\n•	Working with blend modes\r\n•	Advanced particle system design\r\n•	Working with templates\r\n•	Masking methods\r\n•	Keyframing techniques\r\n•	Integration with other Final Cut Studio applications','This three-day, hands-on course will familiarize students with Motion, Apple\'s revolutionary software for motion graphics design. This comprehensive course covers working with Motion\'s Real-Time Design engine and interface, behavior-based animation, parameter behaviors, blend modes, advanced particle system design, advanced title animation, working with templates, chroma key techniques, masking methods, advanced 3D features, working with audio, keyframing, and integration.\r\n\r\nKnowledge of Mac OS X and basic computer navigation.\r\nBasic knowledge of Final Cut Pro 7 is required.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=114&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111116153015','',''),(76,3,'Color 101:','color-101','An Introduction to Colour Correction in Final Cut Studio','This Apple accredited course introduces students to Final Cut Studio\'s colour correcting capabilities. Start with the basics of colour correction in Final Cut Pro and move on to the fine points of secondary grading in Color. The course is designed for those who prefer hands-on and interactive instruction to best explore the functionality. ','This two-day hands-on course will familiarize students with the colour correcting capabilities of Final Cut Studio. Start with the basics of colour balancing and correction, and move on to the fine points of secondary grading, including scene matching, using vignettes to isolate and track regions, creating advanced colour effects and “looks,” skin tone adjustments, adjusting the composition and framing of a shot, and much more.\r\n•	Navigating the Color Rooms\r\n•	Understanding Waveform and Vectorscopes\r\n•	Using Trackers\r\n•	Colour Correcting Contrast\r\n•	Colour Correcting for Brightness \r\nWorking with Vignettes','This course is designed for existing Final Cut Pro users who want to learn more about the colour correction and grading capabilities of Final Cut Studio. The course is designed for those who prefer hands-on and interactive instruction to best explore the functionality. \r\nKnowledge of Mac OS X and basic computer navigation. \r\nBasic knowledge of Final Cut Pro 7 is required.\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=111&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111116152835','',''),(77,3,'Final Cut Pro 101:','final-cut-pro-101','Introduction to Final Cut Pro','This Apple accredited course is designed for anyone looking to edit professional-quality video with Final Cut Pro and who prefers hands-on and interactive instruction to best explore its functionality.','Start with basic video editing techniques and work all the way through Final Cut Pro\'s powerful advanced features. Learn to mark and edit clips, mix sound, add titles, create transitions, apply filters, and more.\r\n•	Marking clips, using insert, overwrite and drag-and-drop editing\r\n•	Trimming edit points\r\n•	Using Ripple, Roll, and Extend edits as well as the Slip and Slide tools\r\n•	Applying filters and changing Motion properties.\r\n•	Audio editing and audio creation\r\n•	Finishing and final output\r\nTopics include basic setup, customizing preferences and settings, capturing video and audio, various editing and trimming techniques, Ripple, Roll, Slip, and Slide tools, audio editing and audio creation, finishing and final output.\r\n','This three day, hands-on course teaches students to perform basic editing functions while becoming familiar with the Final Cut Pro user interface. In this course, you will cut a scene from the TNT television series Leverage, create a promo for Seaworld\'s Believe documentary, as well as master filters and effects as you edit a segment of Playing for Change, the international music-creation event. \r\nKnowledge of Mac OS X and basic computer navigation\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=113&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111116153137','',''),(78,3,'DVD Studio Pro 101:','dvd-studio-pro-101','Introduction to DVD Studio Pro','This Apple accredited course aims to teach students how to create, design and encode professional DVDs using Apple’s DVD Studio Pro software. ','This three day, hands-on course delves into the world of DVD authoring with DVD Studio Pro 4. In this comprehensive course, students will learn everything they need to create a professional DVD title. This course guides students through every aspect of DVD authoring, from initial storyboarding to burning and replication.\r\n•	Creating menus in DVD Studio Pro\r\n•	Simulating discs\r\n•	Working with storyboards\r\n•	Creating buttons on menus\r\n•	Creating slideshows\r\n•	Encoding assets and bit budgeting\r\nUsing compelling media and a real-world production workflow, students will learn how to create amazing MPEG 2 video with Compressor as well as create eye-popping motion menus directly in DVD Studio Pro 4. Students will also “author” a DVD by creating buttons, interactive links, slideshows, playlists and even adding alternate audio stream and camera angles.\r\n','This three-day course is designed for those who want to learn the basics of authoring professional quality DVDs with DVD Studio Pro 4 and who prefer hands-on, interactive instruction to explore its full functionality. Knowledge of Mac OS X and basic computer navigation.\r\nSome knowledge of Final Cut Pro 7 is recommended. \r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=112&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111116153345','',''),(79,2,'Fashion Design for Intermediates','fashion-design-for-intermediates','','– To gain an in-depth knowledge of the fashion and textiles industries\r\n– To research trend themes and create inspirational storyboards for a specific market level/sector\r\n– To learn how to develop and use inspirational visual research to realise design ideas\r\n– To develop initial ideas into innovative contemporary designs for fashion garments and accessories, using professional methods of presentation.\r\n\r\n','Moving forward from the Fashion Design for Beginners course you will be given the opportunity to develop your own individual design theme. On the\r\ncourse you will:\r\n\r\n– Further develop awareness of styling directions, trends, markets and the sector as a whole – Use visual research to develop innovative garment designs to create a capsule collection of garments and accessories.\r\n– Further experiment with illustration techniques to apply professional methods to the presentation of your capsule collection.\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course you will have a set of storyboards for a season’s collection along with a portfolio of development ideas, sketches and research.','Intermediate level - although the course is ideally suitable for those with some background in fashion or textiles design, keen beginners are also welcome. The course is ideal for learners wishing to progress from A-level to BA Hons/FdA Fashion courses.\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=94&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222122839','',''),(80,3,'Dreamweaver for Intermediates','dreamweaver-for-intermediates','','You will:\r\n– Develop a clear picture of the benefits of a web presence in professional life\r\n– Develop an understanding of web-standards, constraints and processes involved in web design\r\n– Develop skills with a WYSIWYG web design tool\r\n– Design, build, upload and promote a website in support of your professional goals.','Intermediate students who have prior experience of using Dreamweaver. An ideal follow-on from Dreamweaver for Beginners.','This course will advance your knowledge and skills of maintaining a website through Adobe Dreamweaver. Over the 8 weeks the course will include, but is not limited to:\r\n\r\n– Introduction to PHP & databases\r\n– Introduction to Actionscript\r\n– Creating forms for websites\r\n– Further Photoshop for the web\r\n– Installing Open Source software\r\n– Introduction to JavaScript and JQuery\r\n\r\nDuring the course you will also look at social networking, RSS feeds, podcasts and webcasts. By the end of the course you will have gained further knowledge of Dreamweaver and a website of your own design.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=115&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222113959','',''),(81,4,'Making Music with Computers','making-music-with-computers','','The main aims of the course is to introduce you to studio software, to create and mix beats, use the interface as well as adding effects onto your track.','Beginners','Over the ten weeks you will be introduced to studio software. \r\nThrough hands-on workshops, you will cover the following:\r\n\r\n– Initial introduction to the software and its tools\r\n– Exploring virtual instruments\r\n– Introduction to virtual synthesis\r\n– Sequencing and automation\r\n– MIDI and sample manipulation \r\n–  Effects\r\n–  Building a Track\r\n–  Full track production\r\n– Looking at Logic (re-wire)\r\n– Studio testing & mastering\r\n\r\nYou will have the opportunity to work on your own implementing the skills you have learnt throughout the course, by the end of which you will have produced a track of your own.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=108&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222120303','',''),(82,19,'Beginners Course to Fashion Decorations','beginners-course-to-fashion-decorations','Young Peoples Course','Interested in or thinking about a career in the Fashion Industry?....Get a head start by joining this short course where you will experiment with design ideas.  \r\n\r\n','5 week course for 9 to 13 year olds\r\n\r\n\r\n10% discount applies if you have enrolled on the taster course as well.\r\n\r\nConcession rate £50.00\r\n\r\nFor concession rates, please contact our office on 01707 285327 - These include children on free school meals, parents on job seekers allowance and/or income support or pensions credit.','Each week you’ll work on customising and decorating an accessory.  Learn tricks of the trade from designers from the industry.   A great start to understanding the world of fashion design.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=175&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20120120132733','',''),(83,18,'Fashion – Funk Up Your T-shirt','fashion-funk-up-your-tshirt','Young Peoples Taster Course','Customise that boring t-shirt!  We’ll give you tips from top designers, trade secrets and professional support to help you customise and design your own unique t-shirt which you couldn’t buy in any shop.\r\n\r\nNB: For this course you will need to bring along a plain white t-shirt.  We will provide all the other materials and accessories','1 day taster course for 9 to 13 year olds','You’ll enjoy this so much that you will want to enrol on our 5 week short course (10% discount applies to the 5 week course if you enrol on the taster as well).\r\n\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=174&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20120120132840','',''),(84,19,'Flash Games','flash-games','Young Peoples Course','This excellent course has been designed to inspire anyone who wants to learn to create, design and play their very own animated game. Our experienced tutors will teach you the basics of Flash.  You will compose your storyline; develop the rules of the game and import sound and images.    You’ll develop your characters, think about timelines and add sound effects as well as working on the physics of the game – moving, jumping, bouncing and falling.','7 week course for 12 to 17 year olds\r\n\r\nConcession rate £70.00\r\n\r\nFor concession rates, please contact our office on 01707 285327 - These include children on free school meals, parents on job seekers allowance and/or income support or pensions credit.\r\n\r\n','A fantastic insight and head start into developing a career in animated games or just show it off to your friends.\r\n\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=176&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20120120132757','',''),(85,19,'Kids and Dads','kids-and-dads','Young Peoples Course','This fantastic 4 week course is aimed at quality time and quality fun for both kids and dads (or mum’s if you’d prefer!).  All of the four courses have been developed to help you experiment, be creative but above all have fun together whilst utilising our fantastic tutors and facilities.  You’ll come away with some awesome artworks that you’ll treasure as you’ve made it together.','4 week course for 8 - 14 years old with one parent\r\n\r\n10% discount applies to this course if you have enrolled on the taster course as well.\r\n\r\nConcession rate £60.00\r\n\r\nFor concession rates, please contact our office on 01707 285327 - These include children on free school meals, parents on job seekers allowance and/or income support or pensions credit.','The four courses include:\r\n\r\nRe-vamping a piece of furniture – you’ll work together to decorate, customise and finish a piece of furniture which you’ll take home for your childs bedroom.\r\n\r\nDark-room photography – work together in the darkroom to create interesting photograms, no one will be the same and it’s something you can frame as a keep-sake.\r\n\r\nLarge scale sculpture – don’t worry you don’t need to be a sculptor, this workshop will help you work together to create something enormous which you can re-construct at home or in the garden.\r\n\r\nMatching t-shirts – work together to create your own unique t-shirts which can be matching or otherwise but we’re sure you will wear them together with pleasure.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=172&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20120120132815','',''),(86,18,'Kids and Dads - Taster','kids-and-dads-taster','Young Peoples Taster Course','Quality time and quality fun for both kids and dads (or mums if you’d prefer).  Come along to our taster session and play our range of percussion instruments (google Gamelan – you’ll be impressed!).  Our tutor will guide you through 2-3 musical pieces.   Don’t worry you don’t need to have a musical bone in your body….it’s all about having fun!\r\n\r\n','1 day taster course for 8 to 14 year olds and one parent.','You’ll enjoy this so much that you will want to enrol on our 4 week short course (10% discount applies to the 4 week course if you enrol on the taster as well.\r\n\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=171&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20120120132855','',''),(87,1,'Experimental Knitting','experimental-knitting','','Knitting is back in vogue! This course is for anyone who wants to be more adventurous with their basic skills.  As long as you can do basic stitches and want to learn more, then this is the course for you. \r\n\r\n','Anyone who already has basic knitting skills and wants to be more adventurous whilst enjoying socialising and experimenting in a group environment','We will help you to experiment, encourage the use of unconventional materials and help you consider the options of exploring scale and processes.\r\n\r\nThese group sessions will help you develop your skills further whilst considering the use of unusual materials such as wire, t-shirts and carrier bags.  We will also help you consider scale by mixing yarns, using giant multi-strand knitting and considering usage and art-based ideas.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=127&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222154519','',''),(88,17,'Experimental Knitting - Taster','experimental-knitting-taster','','This taster course is designed to develop your passion for hand knitting, colour and texture.','Anyone who already has basic knitting skills and wants to be more adventurous whilst enjoying socialising and experimenting in a group environment.\r\n\r\nWe know you\'ll enjoy this so much that you\'ll definitely want to come back for more - so why not book on our 4 week course with a 10% discount if you enrol on this taster.','Beginners will be encouraged to develop knitting skills using unusual methods and  improvers and advanced knitters will be introduced to ways that contemporary knitting can used within an art context as well as for fun and creative fashion accessories.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=129&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222155021','',''),(89,17,'Introduction to Ceramics','introduction-to-ceramics','Taster','If you’ve always wanted to have a go at ceramics!  Then this is your chance. you will be introduced to a range of techniques and processes with expert advice and you will make your own ceramic plate which you’ll be able to show off to your family and friends.','The course is designed for both beginners and students experienced in working with clay. \r\n','We’re sure you’ll enjoy this 2.5 hour class, so why not enrol on our 8 week course with a 10% discount; if you have booked on the taster session, you can develop further and learn about coiling, pinching, slips and glazes and have fun with decorative techniques.  ','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=117&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222155215','',''),(90,17,'Introduction to Glass Art','introduction-to-glass-art','Taster','This taster course will introduce you to the processes of creative glass making.  You will be encouraged to experiment with your design and make your own tile, dish or wall hanging to fire in our kiln.','We know you’ll enjoy this course, so why not book on our 8-week course with a 10% discount, if you have booked on the taster session. You will experiment with kiln formed pieces and learn skills in design, colour and construction.','This course will give you a taster of the world of creative glass making.  You\'ll be introduced to the processes and shown examples of work you will be able to produce.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=116&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222155453','',''),(91,17,'Jewellery for Beginners','jewellery-for-beginners','Taster','Have you ever wanted to make or design your own jewellery but didn’t know where to begin?  Well, this is your chance to have a go and experiment with your own ideas, all under the guidance of a professional.  You don’t need any special skills, just an eye for what you like and we’ll help you design and make your own pendant in a base metal.  Take it home, add a chain and you’re a jewellery designer!\r\n\r\nIf you want to upgrade then you can make your own design in silver for an extra £7 – just give us one week’s notice and we’ll buy the raw materials in for you.','Anyone who wants to have a go at jewellery design.  This beginners’ taster course is designed to give you the skills to make one item however we’re sure you’ll get the bug and want to carry on making.','You’ll initially work on a design, then be given all the tools to make the pendant and then we’ll show you polishing and finishing techniques.\r\n\r\nYou’ll love this 2.5 hour course so much that you’ll want to join our beginners short course with a complimentary 10% discount if you book on the taster session.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=118&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222160807','',''),(92,4,'Singing for Beginners','singing-for-beginners','','You don’t need to read music and there is no solo singing.  It’s all about having fun, busting your stress and boosting your energy.  A great workshop for anyone who wants to find their voice in a non-intimidating environment.  The course will help you grow in confidence and volume.  \r\n\r\nThis is your chance to face the music and claim your voice back now!','For anyone who wants to develop their singing voice from absolute beginners, the totally terrified or someone who wants to develop further in a fun and unintimidating environment.','This course will help you strengthen your voice and your confidence in singing.  Our professional tutor will lead you through exercises to help you develop your voice, will coach in breathing techniques and take you through songs and exercises to help broaden your range.   \r\n\r\nThe course will be set in a comfortable group environment with no solos, intimidation or embarrassment, just energising fun and practice for the future.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=168&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222161227','',''),(93,17,'Singing for Beginners - Taster','singing-for-beginners-taster','','You don’t need to read music and there is no solo singing.  It’s all about having fun, busting your stress and boosting your energy.  A great taster session for anyone who wants to find their voice in a non-intimidating environment.\r\n\r\nYou’ll have so much fun you won’t want to stop, so join our 4-week course with a 10% discount if you have booked on our taster class.','Were you told to mime in the school choir, laughed at last time you tried Karaoke or think you can\'t sing?  Or do you want to try strengthening your voice by being coached by a professional? Then this is your chance to face the music and do something about it.  Grow in confidence and volume - book now!  \r\n\r\nClaim your voice back now because you are worth it!\r\n\r\nWe know you\'ll enjoy this so much that you\'ll definitely want to come back for more - so why not book on our 4 week course with a 10% discount.  You\'ll learn how to warm up, project your voice and gain confidence whilst having fun and enjoying yourself. \r\n','We will help you find your singing voice, or work with you to strengthen what you already have in a comfortable group environment with no solos or embarassment just energising fun and practice for the future. ','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=119&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222161616','',''),(94,4,'Ukulele – For the Complete Beginner','ukulele-for-the-complete-beginner','','Ukuleles are supposed to be the easiest instrument to play (apart from the triangle!!) and once you’ve been shown how to get going I’m sure you will agree.  You don’t need to read music, all you need is a ukulele, a slight sense of rhythm and a desire to join in and have fun.  A voice is also useful (good, bad or indifferent acceptable) to help keep up the timing and to make things more fun.\r\n\r\nEverything is done within the group, so no solo’s, no intimidation and good fun, with lots of noise and with everyone joining in.........you’ll be impressed with how good it will sound.','Beginners who like to have fun','The course will start with the three basic skills - rhythm, chords (very easy, only 4 strings) and chord changes.  You’ll also learn to tune your Uke and have fun with strumming.  As the weeks progress you will expand the chords you use which means you’ll be able to learn more tunes to play.\r\n\r\nYou’ll also be given website details of where to obtain ukulele chords and tabs so that you’ll be able to pick out your favorite songs, new and old, to play along with at home.\r\n\r\nA much more pleasant experience by playing in a group environment and lots more fun (the person writing this learned this way and within a few months is playing and performing in a group – so it can be done!)','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=126&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222161818','',''),(95,17,'Ukulele – For the Complete Beginner - Taster','ukulele-for-the-complete-beginner-taster','','Do you have a Ukulele or did you get one for Christmas?  This course will introduce you to the basics of playing within a group – great advantage for beginners - and will teach you at least two tunes to practice on your own at home.  You don\'t need to read music, all you need is a slight sense of rhythm and you\'ll be well away.','Beginners who like to have fun','This taster course will give you your first lesson in playing the Ukulele.   Your tutor will give you all the basic instructions you need to get you playing quickly and everyone will be strumming one or two tunes by the time you go home.  \r\n\r\nYou will also receive links to websites where you can obtain easy Ukulele chords and tabs so that you can pick out your favourite tunes and strum along.  Everything is explained in easy steps and you’ll be surprised how quickly you will develop.\r\n\r\nThis course will be followed on by a 5-week course in late spring where you can develop these skills further and enjoy playing and singing (optional) in a small friendly group.  A 10% discount will apply if you have booked on the taster session','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=121&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222162050','',''),(96,5,'Art Therapy for Beginners','art-therapy-for-beginners','','This two day short course gives participants an opportunity to explore the therapeutic use of art through practical and experiential workshops.\r\n\r\n','','Day 1 will focus on communication, non-verbal and verbal, within art therapy\r\n\r\nDay 2 will give the participants a chance to undertake experiential workshops including individual and group experiences.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=67&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222162826','',''),(97,5,'Drawn to Dialogue','drawn-to-dialogue','','This intensive three-day, studio-based drawing masterclass combines Art Therapy and Fine Art approaches to drawing practice.','','The focus of the masterclass is \"Moving Along ..\"\r\n\r\nIt aims to look attentively at the movement and pace of change (slow? sudden? gradual?) in the moment-to-moment activity of drawing and to move towards developing a systematic and analytic method for looking at transformational change processes. What is the person who draws doing?  Why?\r\n\r\nThere will be:\r\n\r\n*  Practical workshops\r\n\r\n*  Reflective practice\r\n\r\n*  Use of life models and time-based digital technology.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=68&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222163556','',''),(98,8,'Life Drawing for Sixth Formers','life-drawing-for-sixth-formers','','The aim of this course is to give students applying for higher education an understanding of the application process, from creating an ideal portfolio to writing personal statements to interview tips.','Sixth Formers','An ideal course for those wishing to study Art & Design courses in higher education. After an initial introduction to the course, the materials required and contextual studies, you will emphasise and work on areas such as: \r\n\r\n– Draughtsmanship\r\n\r\n– Composition\r\n\r\n– Tones\r\n\r\n– Foreshortening\r\n\r\n– Interpretation\r\n\r\nThe course will help you encourage your awareness in order to develop your own style. You will base your work on a life model each week. \r\n\r\nBy the end of the course you will have a portfolio of work ideal for interviews.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=69&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222163932','',''),(99,8,'Preparing Your Art & Design Portfolio','preparing-your-art-and-design-portfolio','','The aim of this course is to give students applying for higher education an understanding of the application process, from creating an ideal portfolio to writing personal statements to interview tips.','Sixth formers','This course will introduce you to the basic components required for degree level study in art & design disciplines. Over the 10 weeks, the course will include, but is not limited to: \r\n\r\n– A look at the key concepts of art & design\r\n\r\n– Guidance on application forms & personal statements\r\n\r\n– Tips for the interview process\r\n\r\n– Opportunities to develop your portfolio\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course you will have a body of work which will be a valuable addition to your portfolio as well as an understanding of portfolio preparation for the emerging artist or designer.','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=70&deptid=13&catid=20','course_image20111222164319','',''),(100,18,'Young Peoples Workshop - The Many of Aspects Me','young-peoples-workshop-the-many-of-aspects-me','','ThisA great three-day course where you will produce your own short film based on ……YOU!  \r\n\r\nYour three days with us will include:-\r\n\r\nA short screening of films to inspire you\r\nChoosing a style for your own film such as Film Noir, Anthology Film or documentary\r\nChoosing to become a fictional character or basing your idea on aspects of your life. \r\nWorking in a small team to develop your work\r\nStoryboarding, scripting and mood setting\r\nFilming, directing and lighting\r\nPost production.\r\n\r\nYou’ll come away with a short ‘self portrait’ movie for your portfolio.','This workshop is for children between the ages of 13 to 16','Workshop information\r\n\r\nAll our activities take advantage of our amazing facilities and technology and are run by a team of industry professionals who are experienced at working with young people.  Our workshops are designed to be fun and exciting with the emphasis on learning and experimentation.\r\n\r\nAll of the workshops run from 10.00am to 4.00pm, however registration takes place from 9.30am in the Art and Design Gallery. Everyone needs to be there by 9.50 in preparation for the class.\r\n\r\nWe welcome applications from young people with disabilities.  It is helpful to tell us about your disability when you apply so that we can discuss your needs with you prior to the start of a workshop.\r\n\r\nVenue\r\n\r\nAll our courses are held at the University of Hertfordshire’s College Lane campus.  To view our location information please visit go.herts.ac.uk/findus   We will however send you a map and full instructions regarding what to bring with you once you’ve booked a course.\r\n\r\nParking\r\n\r\nCar park 9 is available for dropping off and collecting for the workshops.\r\n\r\nCost\r\n\r\nAll materials and facilities are included in the price of each course.\r\n\r\nConcession rates are available for most workshops, please call our office for details.\r\n\r\nCourse can be booked on line at go.herts.ac.uk/creativeshortcourses however we also require a written application to ensure we have full contact information and details of any special requirements.  We will send this in the post to you.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nFurther information\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions or need any assistance please contact our Short Course Office on:-\r\n\r\n01707 285327 or view our full offer on www.go.herts.ac.uk/creativeshortcourses\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nWe run a huge range of courses for adults too – please see our website for details.\r\n\r\nSchool of Creative Arts\r\nShort Course Office\r\nCollege Lane\r\nHatfield\r\nHerts AL10 9AB\r\n','http://store.herts.ac.uk/browse/extra_info.asp?compid=1&modid=5&prodid=319&deptid=13&catid=86','course_image20120522132113','',''),(101,17,'Alternative Analogue Photography - Beginners - Black & White Processing - Summer Taster','alternative-analogue-photography-beginners-black-and-white-processing-summer-taster','','On this one day course students will work in traditional black and white print using both fibre based and acrylic based papers, will be using lith printing and lith re-development.','Anyone who wishes to sample black & white processing and alternative methods.','In this course you will learn how to use salt and cyantypes materials to produce fantastic prints to take home and display.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/Alternative-Analogue-Photography-Beginners--Black--White-Processing-Summer-Tasters_details.cfm','course_image20120530121639','',''),(102,17,'Alternative Analogue Photography - Beginners - Pin Hole Cameras - Summer Taster','alternative-analogue-photography-beginners-pin-hole-cameras-summer-taster','','This taster course will focus on creative development of the possibilities of pin hole photography. This includes digital and analogue cameras.','From beginners to experienced students including school leavers who need to upgrade their skill level to help with their portfolio.','On this one-day course you will start by building your own pin-hole camera out of everyday found objects and will be developing positive and negative images from this.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/alternative-analogue-photography-beginners-pin-hole-cameras-summer-taster_details.cfm','course_image20120530121703','',''),(103,17,'Introduction to Ceramic Jewellery - Summer Taster','introduction-to-ceramic-jewellery-summer-taster','','This taster course will introduce students to some of the techniques used in making beautiful ceramic jewellery.','Suitable for complete beginners and for those with previous ceramic experience.','This taster course will give students an insight into the many techniques which can be used when making ceramic jewellery. This taster session will focus on making a finished ceramic pendant or brooch. The course is taught through demonstrations, experimentation, discussion and one to one tutor support.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/introduction-to-ceramic-jewellery-summer-taster_details.cfm','course_image20120530121732','',''),(104,17,'Introduction to Glass Art (Kiln Formed Glass) - Summer Taster','introduction-to-glass-art-kiln-formed-glass-summer-taster','','This taster course will introduce you to the processes of creative glass making. You will be encouraged to experiment with your design and make your own tile, dish or wall hanging to fire in our kiln.','We know you’ll enjoy this course, so why not book on our 8-week course with a 10% discount, if you have booked on the taster session. You will experiment with kiln formed pieces and learn skills in design, colour and construction.','This course will give you a taster of the world of creative glass making. You\'ll be introduced to the processes and shown examples of work you will be able to produce.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/introduction-to-glass-art-kiln-formed-glass-summer-taster_details.cfm','course_image20120530121755','',''),(105,17,'Introduction to Glass Jewellery - Summer Taster','introduction-to-glass-jewellery-summer-taster','','This course has been designed to introduce students to a variety of decorative techniques within kiln formed glass jewellery.','The course is designed for anyone wanting to experiment with a variety of fused glass techniques to produce a range of contemporary jewellery. The course is suitable for both complete beginners and for those with previous glass experience who want to extend their skills.','The course introduces students to a range of techniques to create glass jewellery pieces including kiln carving, surface decoration, frits, stringer design and powder and pattern techniques.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/introduction-to-glass-jewellery-summer-taster_details.cfm','course_image20120530121841','',''),(106,17,'Introduction to Japanese Ink Painting (Sumi E) - Summer Taster','introduction-to-japanese-ink-painting-sumi-e-summer-taster','','This course will introduce students to the principles of Japanese Zen Ink painting.','The course is ideal for beginners or experienced students who want to learn a new skill.','You will learn the basic brush strokes, understand the traditions of the philosophy but most importantly produce beautiful ink paintings.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/introduction-to-japanese-ink-painting-sumi-e-summer-taster_details.cfm','course_image20120530121917','',''),(107,17,'Introduction to Jewellery Enamelling - Summer Taster','introduction-to-jewellery-enamelling-summer-taster','','This course will give you a chance to produce a beautiful pendant or brooch using the processes of jewellery enamelling.\r\n\r\nStudents will learn basic enamelling alongside basic bench skills. These skills will enable you to produce a simple pendant or brooch which you can mount and wear with pride.','This course is ideal for beginners or experienced jewellery makers who would like to learn a new skill.','This course will cover basic enamelling skills such as applying powder and wet process enamels, using the kilns and torches.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/introduction-to-jewellery-enamelling-summer-taster_details.cfm','course_image20120530121946','',''),(108,17,'Introduction to Life Drawing - Summer Taster','introduction-to-life-drawing-summer-taster','','A great opportunity to try life drawing! The course covers the fundamentals of form and structure of the human figure and introduces you to the primary building blocks of mark making.','This course is ideal for anyone who wants to try life drawing for the first time or for people who would like to have another go if it’s been a long time.','This course has been designed to introduce students to drawing and painting from a life model. Our tutor will give you the confidence to start mark making and It will help you consider proportions, tone and composition.\r\n\r\nThe fundamentals of mark making from a life model including proportions, composition and tonal values.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/introduction-to-life-drawing-summer-taster_details.cfm','course_image20120530122006','',''),(109,17,'Introduction to Printmaking - Summer Taster','introduction-to-printmaking-summer-taster','','To offer a taster session to anyone who is interested in trying printmaking. Students will receive a demonstration of monoprints and collograph, to enable them to produce their own product.','This course is suitable for beginners or people with some prior experience wishing to revisit printmaking.','The course will cover:\r\n\r\nMonoprint -applying ink to a flat surface to achieve one off prints\r\n\r\nCollograph- using a cardboard plate to produce an intaglio type print','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/introduction-to-printmaking-summer-taster_details.cfm','course_image20120530122032','',''),(110,17,'Introduction to Sculpture - Summer Taster','introduction-to-sculpture-summer-taster','','A great opportunity to sample the world of sculpture. Starting with clay modelling our tutor will take you through the process of creating a small portrait head and will explain other sculptural techniques which you could develop through one of our short courses.','Beginners to sculpture or anyone who wishes to experiment with 3D modelling.','Full instruction and support will be given to produce a small portrait head which will involve working in clay directly from a live model.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/introduction-to-sculpture-summer-taster_details.cfm','course_image20120530122108','',''),(111,17,'Introduction to Stained Glass - Summer Taster','introduction-to-stained-glass-summer-taster','','A taster day introducing students to some of the simpler techniques used in the making of a stained glass panel.','For beginners who would like to try making a small piece of stained glass before thinking of moving on to larger pieces of work.','The copper foiling technique was pioneered by Louis Comfort Tiffany in the USA in the nineteenth century. Primarily used for decorative pieces, lamps and sun catchers, the techniques learned are also applicable to making larger leaded windows. This one day course gives students a basic introduction.\r\n\r\nA brief introduction to designing for stained glass\r\n\r\nLearning to cut coloured glass accurately\r\n\r\nApplying copper foil tape\r\n\r\nSoldering\r\n\r\nNB for the purpose of this course, students will be able to buy all necessary materials from the tutor. Depending upon your design this will cost no more than £30.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/introduction-to-stained-glass-summer-taster_details.cfm','course_image20120530122125','',''),(112,17,'Introduction to Watercolour - Dramatic Skies - Summer Taster','introduction-to-watercolour-dramatic-skies-summer-taster','','This course aims to introduce you to Watercolour Painting through developing a Dramatic Sky!','Ideal for beginners and is a taster for the eight week course which follows on.','This one day course focuses on a number of techniques to develop a dramatic skyline and its shadow upon the landscape.\r\n\r\nAfter a brief examination of some examples of dramatic skies we will be working with the \'Wet in Wet\' technique on large pieces of paper and experiementing with colour and shadow. We will see how the surface effects the paint and how the size of brush makes a difference. We will be adding detail and then pick out the shadows on the mountains or fields below.\r\n\r\nThis is an impact course designed for you to gain as much detail as you can inthe short period of time!','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/introduction-to-watercolour-dramatic-skies-summer-taster_details.cfm','course_image20120530122144','',''),(113,17,'Ukulele (for the Complete Beginner) - Summer Taster','ukulele-for-the-complete-beginner-summer-taster','','Do you have a Ukulele or did you get one for Christmas? This course will introduce you to the basics of playing within a group – great advantage for beginners - and will teach you at least two tunes to practice on your own at home. You don\'t need to read music, all you need is a slight sense of rhythm and you\'ll be well away.','Beginners who want to learn the basics about their ukulele!','This taster course will give you your first lesson in playing the Ukulele. Your tutor will give you all the basic instructions you need to get you playing quickly and everyone will be strumming one or two tunes by the time you go home.\r\n\r\nYou will also receive links to websites where you can obtain easy Ukulele chords and tabs so that you can pick out your favourite tunes and strum along. Everything is explained in easy steps and you’ll be surprised how quickly you will develop.\r\n\r\nThis course will be followed on by a 6-week coursewhere you can develop these skills further and enjoy playing and singing (optional) in a small friendly group. A 10% discount will apply if you have booked on the taster session.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/ukulele-for-the-complete-beginner-summer-taster_details.cfm','course_image20120530122223','',''),(114,6,'Alternative Analogue Photography - Pin Hole Cameras - Summer Course','alternative-analogue-photography-pin-hole-cameras-summer-course','','This course will cover the creation of your own camera from everyday objects, through to producing your own photographic paper (Salt Printing).','From beginners to experienced students including school leavers who need to upgrade their skill level to help with their portfolio.','This two day course will extend upon the experience of the taster course and will focus on the continuing creative development of the possibilities of pin hole photography. This includes digital pin hole and the development of prints.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/alternative-analogue-photography-pin-hole-cameras-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530121340','',''),(115,6,'Art Workshop - Summer Course','art-workshop-summer-course','','To develop your creativity further and improve existing skills through working from a life model or any subject matter of your own choice.','Suitable for all levels of experience, as a broad range of skills are taught. ','Working from the life model provided, still life set- ups,or own choice of subject matter, you will be encouraged to improve your existing skills and to develop your creativity further, in either 2D and 3D or both. \r\n\r\nThe course will cover the following topics: \r\n\r\nskills in draughtsmanship, line, tone, form and composition\r\nthe use of colour to create harmony and balance\r\nthe rhythms and movement in the composition\r\nthe use of a wide variety of 2D media, traditional and non traditional\r\nhow to build a 3D image in clay, wire, card\r\n\r\nStudents will be shown how to use less traditional media and materials such as collage, sticks, sponges etc. And will be encouraged to experiment and develop an individual style and approach to their work through group discussions and reference to relevant artists.\r\n','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/Art-Workshop--Summer-Course_details.cfm','course_image20120530122347','',''),(116,6,'Ceramic Jewellery (for Beginners / Intermediates) - Summer Course','ceramic-jewellery-for-beginners-intermediates-summer-course','','To introduce students to a variety of decorative techniques within contemporary ceramic jewellery making.','The course is suitable for both complete beginners and for those with previous ceramic experience.','The course introduces students to a range of techniques to create unique jewellery pieces including press moulding, slip trailing, surface manipulation, construction and modelling.\r\n\r\nThe course is designed for anyone wanting to experiment with a variety of ceramic techniques to produce a range of contemporary jewellery.\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course students will have produced a range of unique jewellery pieces including necklaces, pendants, brooches and rings.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/ceramic-jewellery-for-beginners-intermediates-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530122548','',''),(117,6,'Ceramics - Raku Firing - Summer Course','ceramics-raku-firing-summer-course','','The course will cover the history and background of raku firing, making ceramics for raku and the firing process of the work produced.','For students who want to experience the excitement and drama of this unique method.\r\n\r\nAll levels from beginners to experienced.','To experience the making and firing process to produce raku finishes.\r\n\r\nFirst day: Introduction to raku and its history and background. Basic forming techniques and the use of colours on the ceramic.\r\n\r\nSecond day: Glazing and all the process of raku firing.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/ceramics-raku-firing-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530145232','',''),(118,6,'Ceramics - Summer Course','ceramics-summer-course','','This course introduces students to different making processes, design and practical considerations. It gives students an opportunity to develop their own visual ideas and creative identity. ','The course is designed for both beginners and students experienced in working with clay.','Week by week you will be taken through the various processes of ceramics and pottery beginning with the design process. After an initial introduction to the workshop and a health and safety demonstration, you will be taken through processes such as:\r\n\r\nCoiling\r\n\r\nSlab building\r\n\r\nPinching\r\n\r\nSurface decoration\r\n\r\nScreen printing\r\n\r\nRaku firing\r\n\r\nYou can work on your own projects with guidance from the tutor. By the end of the course you will have a range of ceramic pieces of your own design.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/Ceramics--Summer-Course_details.cfm','course_image20120530145459','',''),(119,6,'Confidence in Computer Music Sequencing - Summer Course','confidence-in-computer-music-sequencing-summer-course','','To provide Continuing Professional Development and support for school teachers and instrumental peripatetic tutors.','Anyone wishing to learn more about music technology and feel more confident in the technological environments of modern music classrooms.','An ideal course for music teachers of all levels. The course will provide a balance between theory and practical application of computer music sequencing. On the course you will:\r\n\r\nDevelop sequencing techniques in Cubase, Logic and Reason. All concepts are demonstrated in each program in order to ensure that you can get the most out of your chosen sequencing package in your school\r\n\r\nIntegrating Audio, Midi and Sampling\r\n\r\nAutomating parameters\r\n\r\nEditing techniques\r\n ','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/confidence-in-computer-music-sequencing-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530150524','',''),(120,6,'Confidence in Making Quality Recordings - Summer Course','confidence-in-making-quality-recordings-summer-course','','To provide Continuing Professional Development and support for school teachers and instrumental peripatetic tutors.','Anyone wishing to learn more about music chnology and to gain confidence in the technological environments of modern music classrooms.','An excellent continuation from the Confidence in Computer Music Sequencing course although this course can be taken separately.\r\n\r\nThis course will teach you to:\r\n\r\nSelect the correct microphones and ensure their good placement\r\n\r\nTechniques for recording extra-curricular ensembles, bands, and ensuring that coursework submissions are enhanced by a great recording\r\n\r\nAudio editing and processing','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/confidence-in-making-quality-recordings-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530150825','',''),(121,6,'Creating Lighting Workshop - Summer Course','creating-lighting-workshop-summer-course','','This course will give students that have a basic knowledge in studio lighting, greater understanding and confidence to take their personal work to a new level of creative thinking with practical experience and demonstrations from a professional photographer.','This is idea for amateur and semi professional photographers who wish to taken their basic knowledge in studio lighting a step further.','The course content will include:\r\n\r\nAn introduction to lighting - Shaping light - Explanation of the ways in which light can be shaped and formed using different tools.\r\n\r\nDifferent types of Light - Continuous, Flash, Natural light. \r\n\r\nWhat lighting equipment is available on the market and tips on what to invest in and why. \r\n\r\nPortfolio session - Students show their photographs for an informal session discussing how they lit the photograph and ways in which it could be improved. \r\n\r\nDeconstruct an image and analysing how it was lit. \r\n\r\nStudio set up \r\n\r\nDemonstration of five different ways to light a portrait. (1, One light editorial portrait. 2, Two light - Key light and hard hair light. 3, Using one large Octa softbox. 4, 3 Light set up. 5, 6 light set up. \r\n\r\nPhotography practical - In their own spaces, students photograph their chosen subject matter with support and guidance from professional photographer. \r\n\r\nQuestion and Answer session\r\n\r\nFeedback and Summary. ','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/Creating-Lighting-Workshop--Summer-Course_details.cfm','course_image20120530151408','',''),(122,6,'Drawing & Painting A - Summer Course','drawing-and-painting-a-summer-course','','Working from a life model, or still life if preferred, you will learn basic technical skills in drawing and painting and improve on your existing skills.\r\n\r\nYou will learn how to create interesting compositions in line, tone, and colour, experiment with new methods and media including 3D to develop an individual style and participate in group discussions on work done in class and by other artists. ','Suitable for all levels of experience as a broad range of skills is taught. ','Week by week, and through a step by step approach, you will be taught the basic skills of life drawing and painting, which will cover areas such as:\r\n\r\nHow to draw accurately\r\n\r\nHow to use line\r\n\r\nIntroduction to tone and colour\r\n\r\nCreating interesting compositions\r\n\r\nTechniques of drawing using (but not limited to) pencil, charcoal & pastel\r\n\r\nPainting techniques especially acrylic.\r\n\r\nModelling with clay, wire, card\r\n\r\nIf you have previous experience you will be encouraged to improve your own existing skills and experiment with new methods and media. You can also work on your own theme with help from the tutor. By the end of the course you will have a range of work in different media and an understanding of drawing and skills.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/drawing-painting-a-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530151639','',''),(123,6,'Drawn to Dialogue - Summer Course','drawn-to-dialogue-summer-course','','A three day studio based drawing masterclass designed for artists, art therapists and others interested in drawing as a language.\r\n\r\nThis intensive studio based course combines Fine Art and a psychological approaches to drawing. There will be a focus on extending the practice of drawing through observation to mark making as an internal, personal language.','The course is aimed at artists, teachers, nurses, social care workers or educationalists wishing to update their skills base.','This intensive studio based course combines Fine Art and a psychological approaches to drawing. There will be a focus on extending the practice of drawing through observation to mark making as an internal, personal language.\r\n\r\nSupported by life models, time based digital technology, seminars and a consideration of drawing as a learnt early language, the focus will be to challenge conventions and develop flexible, innovative modes of practice.\r\n\r\nThe course also aims to open up preconceptions or confined ways of art making in order to further student artistic practice outside the course. This will entail looking attentively at the nuances in the activity of drawing which can be stimulated from both inner and outer experience. Although the life model is the initial impetus students are encouraged to move from traditional to less orthodox materials as a means to explore drawing and mark making in its broadest sense.\r\n\r\nThe course moves from observing the figure in space to discovering personally expressed, visual metaphors. An interest in art making is required but no previous experience of life drawing is necessary.\r\nThe course is taught by two tutors, both have experience of drawing and psychological processes related to art practice and its history. A seminar looking at contemporary artist’s approaches to drawing will be included. ','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/drawn-to-dialogue-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530153358','',''),(124,6,'Dreamweaver - Beginners - Summer Course','dreamweaver-beginners-summer-course','','This course aims to provide the skills to create and maintain your own personal website.','No previous experience necessary. Ideal for graphic designers, teachers, artists and photographers or anybody looking to set up their own website.','This course will introduce you to building your website using Adobe Dreamweaver. There will be an initial introduction to the software, the interface and the tools. Over an eight week period the course will cover:\r\n\r\nNavigating Dreamweaver\r\n\r\nMethods of constructing websites\r\n\r\nExamining code and CSS Styles\r\n\r\nImage manipulation for the web\r\n\r\nIntroduction to Adobe Flash for the web\r\n\r\nAdding forms and design elements\r\n\r\nPublishing your site on the web\r\n\r\nImproving your search engine ranking\r\n\r\nThere will be a brief insight into the history and technology of the web. By the end of the course you will have your own website and the skills required to maintain the site. ','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/dreamweaver-beginners-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530153900','',''),(125,6,'Experimental Textiles - Summer Course','experimental-textiles-summer-course','','To introduce students to a wide range of textile techniques and their possibilities.','For students with some knowledge wishing to expand their skill base. Beginners are also welcome.','The course will encourage participants to experiment with scale and process, to produce work that can feed in to other projects or produce a range of samples.\r\n\r\nStudents can experiment with:\r\n\r\nHand dyeing\r\n\r\nResist methods\r\n\r\nHeat press and heat setting techniques\r\n\r\nStitch, embellishing and fabric manipulation\r\n\r\nSilk screen work may be possible depending on experience\r\n\r\nExploring and combining processes to create interesting and varied surfaces which can stand alone or be worked for a specific project. There will be demonstrations and practical workshops which form the basis of the course.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/experimental-textiles-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530154351','',''),(126,6,'Glass Art (Kiln Formed Glass) - Full Week - Summer Course','glass-art-kiln-formed-glass-full-week-summer-course','','An introduction to processes and techniques associated with kiln-formed glass. Students will learn and expand their kiln-formed glass skills while acquiring a better understanding of material, use of colour, texture and finishing techniques. ','The course is designed for both beginners and intermediate students with some experience in working with kiln-formed glass. ','You will be introduced to the processes of creating decorative pieces of glass using kiln-forming techniques. You will have the opportunity to:\r\n\r\nLearn how to cut glass\r\n\r\nUse colouring agents such as metal oxides, enamels and frits\r\n\r\nLearn the processes of slumping glass into or over a mould\r\n\r\nLearn about the firing procedures and annealing cycles\r\n\r\nHow to use the sand blaster\r\n\r\nLearn techniques for finishing\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course you will have a range of glassware pieces from decorative wall panels and small pendants to fruit bowls and coasters.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/glass-art-kiln-formed-glass-full-week-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530154612','',''),(127,6,'Glass Art (Kiln Formed Glass) - Summer Course','glass-art-kiln-formed-glass-summer-course','','An introduction to processes and techniques associated with kiln-formed glass. Students will learn and expand their kiln-formed glass skills while acquiring a better understanding of material, use of colour, texture and finishing techniques.','The course is designed for both beginners and intermediate students with some experience in working with kiln-formed glass.','You will be introduced to the processes of creating decorative pieces of glass using kiln-forming techniques. You will have the opportunity to:\r\n\r\nLearn how to cut glass\r\n\r\nUse colouring agents such as metal oxides, enamels and frits\r\n\r\nLearn the processes of slumping glass into or over a mould\r\n\r\nLearn about the firing procedures and annealing cycles\r\n\r\nHow to use the sand blaster\r\n\r\nLearn techniques for finishing\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course you will have a range of glassware pieces from decorative wall panels and small pendants to fruit bowls and coasters.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/glass-art-kilm-formed-glass-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530155146','',''),(128,6,'Glass Art for Beginners (Kiln Formed Glass) - Summer Course','glass-art-for-beginners-kiln-formed-glass-summer-course','','An introduction to processes and techniques associated with kiln-formed glass.\r\n\r\nStudents will learn and expand their kiln-formed glass skills whilst acquiring a better understanding of material, use of colour, texture and finishing techniques.','The course is designed for both beginners and intermediate students with some experience in working with kiln-formed glass.','You will be introduced to the processes of creating decorative pieces of glass using kiln-forming techniques. You will have the opportunity to:\r\n\r\nLearn how to cut glass\r\n\r\nUse colouring agents such as metal oxides, enamels and frits\r\n\r\nLearn the processes of slumping glass into or over a mould\r\n\r\nLearn about the firing procedures and annealing cycles\r\n\r\nHow to use the sand blaster\r\n\r\nLearn techniques for finishing\r\n\r\nBy the end of the course you will have a range of glassware pieces from decorative wall panels and small pendants to fruit bowls and coasters.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/glass-art-for-beginners-kiln-formed-glass-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530155616','',''),(129,6,'Glass Jewellery for Beginners - Summer Course','glass-jewellery-for-beginners-summer-course','','To introduce students to a variety of decorative techniques within kiln formed glass jewellery.','The course is suitable for both complete beginners and for those with previous glass experience.','The course introduces students to a range of techniques to create glass jewellery pieces including kiln carving, surface decoration, frits and stringer design and powder and pattern techniques.\r\n\r\nThe course is designed for anyone wanting to experiment with a variety of fused glass techniques to produce a range of contemporary jewellery. Throughout the course students will produce a range of jewellery including brooches, pendants, rings and earrings.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/glass-jewellery-for-beginners-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530155817','',''),(130,6,'How to Get the Most From Your iPhone - Summer Course','how-to-get-the-most-from-your-iphone-summer-course','','To enable people to understand the normal day to day operation of their iPhone including setting up iCloud, email, iTunes and other applications.','Aimed at all who wish to gain a greater understanding of their iPhone.','To enable people to synchronise all their contacts and calendar from their mac/ pc to their iPhone along with copying from their older apple devices & other apple devices over cloud. The course will also include setting up accounts to enable downloading of apps and using your iPhone for other social media streams.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/how-to-get-the-most-from-your-iphone-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530160013','',''),(131,6,'How to Use My Digital Camera - Summer Course','how-to-use-my-digital-camera-summer-course','','This course is suitable for anyone who has a digital camera and wishes to learn more about how it functions and how to get the best photographs from it.','This course is suitable for anyone who has a digital camera and wishes to learn more about how it functions and how to get the best photographs from it.','The course will enable students to use controls on their digital cameras such as shutter speed, ISO, white balance and f-stops and create images which you might not have thought possible with your digital camera.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/how-to-use-my-digital-camera-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530160502','',''),(132,6,'Introduction to Art Therapy - Summer Course','introduction-to-art-therapy-summer-course','','This short course gives participants an opportunity to explore the therapeutic use of art through practical and experiential workshops. The course focuses on art therapy as a means to express and explore feelings, both conscious and unconscious, through the medium of art materials.','The course is aimed at arts practitioners, teachers, nurses, social cares workers or educationalists wishing to develop a career in art therapy, early level professionals or others wishing to update their skills base. Previous art making experience is not a pre-requisite.','These two days enable students to engage with the art therapy process by using art materials freely and how in doing so imagery becomes a form of personal expression.\r\n\r\nIt is well known that symbolism plays a part in the interiors of prehistoric caves likewise in individual development drawing comes before writing or verbal language. In this way the course explores the art therapy process as a means of non-verbal, expressive communication giving students an opportunity to make, reflect and discuss how and where art therapy is practiced.\r\n\r\nAlongside the art making process students learn to understand the basic theories that underpin art therapy as a practice with vulnerable people.\r\n\r\nStudents will have the opportunity to explore and reflect on what it means to be part of a therapeutic process and how this can be adapted to different contexts and clients.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/introduction-to-art-therapy-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530160658','',''),(133,6,'Introduction to Drawing and Painting From the Figure - Summer Course','introduction-to-drawing-and-painting-from-the-figure-summer-course','','An introduction to drawing and painting from the figure dealing with proportions through the figure, tonal values, colour mixing and composition.','Anyone who would like to start to learn the art of Life Drawing from a model.','Week 1 - Pencil drawing. Starting with sessions of quick studies, then two longer poses, focusing on proportions through the figure and the importance of the vertical and horizontal.\r\n\r\nWeek 2 – A study session. Students will use either (a) black or white paint or (b) black, white and yellow ochre. To explore tonal values and composition.\r\n\r\nWeek 3 - A study session – students will be using a palette of black, white, yellow ochre and cadmium red with the emphasis on colour mixing and temperature.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/introduction-to-drawing-and-painting-from-the-figure-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530161005','',''),(134,6,'Japanese Ink Painting (Sumi E) for Beginners - Summer Course','japanese-ink-painting-sumi-e-for-beginners-summer-course','','The course will introduce you to the basics of Japanese brush painting and Zen principles learning about specific preparation. Students will explore the 4 treasures (ink, paper, ink stone and brushes). Some calligraphy techniques will be introduced but there will be an emphasis on natural subjects.','This course is suitable for students of all abilities.','The course will introduce you to the basics of Japanese brush painting (sumi e) and Zen principles learning about specific preparation.\r\n\r\nStudents will explore the 4 treasures (ink, paper, ink stone and brushes). Students will be introduced to calligraphy techniques but there will be an emphasis on natural subjects such as: Flowers, Plant, Animals and Landscapes.\r\n\r\nWithin the course students will do calligraphy exercises in:\r\n\r\nkana Character\r\n\r\nPictograms / ideograms\r\n\r\nDemonstrations and hand-outs will guide and encourage you to work with freedom experimenting with the line to create effective brushstrokes. By the end of the course students will have a general idea of Japanese ink painting and will be able to take some interesting brushwork home.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/japanese-ink-painting-sumi-e-for-beginners-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530161220','',''),(135,6,'Make the Most of Your iPad - Summer Course','make-the-most-of-your-ipad-summer-course','','To enable people to understand the normal day to day operation of their iPad which includes setting up iCloud, email, iTunes and other applications.','Anyone who wishes to learn more about their iPad - suitable for beginners.','To empower students to get the most out of their iPad and all its functions. The course will cover how to get the most out of your iPad camera, to synchronise with your other apple devices through iCloud. It will also include setting up accounts to enable you to download apps and using tools for other social media streams.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/make-the-most-of-your-ipad-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530161503','',''),(136,6,'Phase One Master Class - Summer Course','phase-one-master-class-summer-course','','This course aims to offer professionals and keen amateurs the opportunity to utilise Phase One equipment together with supported training. This training seminar will include a mixture of studio work, lectures and hands-on practice. Attendees will have the opportunity to use the P30+ camera systems featuring the Phase One 645DF.','This course is for professionals who are looking to up-skill and keen amateurs who would like to sample a Phase One system with tutor support.','You will receive in-depth tutorials in the following areas:\r\n\r\nPhase One digital backs camera bodies and lenses: Technology inside the Phase One P+ series digital backs.\r\n\r\nPhase One 645DF camera system and lenses: Recommended usage and capabilities.\r\n\r\nThird party cameras: Usage with Phase One digital backs, troubleshooting, and Canon/Nikon tethering.\r\n\r\nComputers: Recommended setups, troubleshooting and maintenance.\r\n\r\nCapture One RAW conversion software: Efficient workflow in Capture One Pro 6, advanced tools, and troubleshooting.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/phase-one-master-class-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530161654','',''),(137,6,'Printmaking (full week) - Summer Course','printmaking-full-week-summer-course','','To introduce and develop printmaking skills as part of a fine art activity.','The activity can be geared to suit your interests and experience, from complete beginners to advanced study.','The course will allow you to uncover printmaking methods and techniques. With practical, hands on experience some of the aspects you will cover include:\r\n\r\nSimple methods of printmaking such as collographs\r\n\r\nEtching\r\n\r\nRelief printing (wood and linocut)\r\n\r\nPainting processes – monoprinting & monotyping\r\n\r\nUsing flat plate and the application of ink\r\n\r\nYou will have the opportunity to focus on one or two methods for your own projects if you wish. By the end of the course you will have an understanding of print processes and a portfolio of work.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/printmaking-full-week-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530161901','',''),(138,6,'Printmaking - Lithography - Summer Course','printmaking-lithography-summer-course','','This course is ideal for people who want to extend their printing skills and portfolio. Lithography is closer to drawing and painting than other printmaking processes. The course entails the process of producing an image on a lithographic plate including printing in black and adding stencilled colour.','This course is ideal for people with some previous experience of drawing and/or printmaking as this would be an advantage.','To introduce students to lithography painting including plate preparation.\r\n\r\nOur tutor will demonstrate the different stages of Lithography print, including producing and processing a black and white drawing on a zinc plate and the addition of colour by a simple stencil technique.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/printmaking-lithography-summer-course_fees.cfm','course_image20120530162421','',''),(139,6,'Printmaking - Summer Course','printmaking-summer-course','','To introduce and develop printmaking skills as part of a fine art activity.','The activity can be geared to suit your interests and experience, from complete beginners to advanced study.','The course will allow you to uncover printmaking methods and techniques. With practical, hands on experience some of the aspects you will cover include:\r\n\r\nSimple methods of printmaking such as collographs\r\n\r\nEtching\r\n\r\nRelief printing (wood and linocut)\r\n\r\nPainting processes\r\n\r\nMonoprinting & monotyping\r\n\r\nUsing flat plate and the application of ink\r\n\r\nYou will have the opportunity to focus on one or two methods for your own projects if you wish. By the end of the course you will have an understanding of print processes and a portfolio of work.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/Printmaking--Summer-Course_details.cfm','course_image20120530162622','',''),(140,6,'Sculpture for Beginners - Summer Course','sculpture-for-beginners-summer-course','','The aims of the course are to encourage students in the appreciation and acquisition of the traditional crafts and knowledge of the practice of sculpture in all its forms.','Suitable for beginners and those with a limited experienceof the world of sculpture.','The course introduces you to sculptural techniques using a range of materials and media. The course will cover areas such as:\r\n\r\nForming figures in a range of material including wire, plaster or clay\r\n\r\nIntroductions to methods such as moulding, casting in wax, plaster and possibly ciment fondu\r\n\r\nExploration of carving and constructing techniques and methods where the facilities of the department allow','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/sculpture-for-beginners-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530162907','',''),(141,6,'Setting up and Marketing Arts Therapies in Schools and CAMHS - Summer Course','setting-up-and-marketing-arts-therapies-in-schools-and-camhs-summer-course','','This course is for art therapists considering working within educational settings and Child and Adolescent Mental Health Services.','The course is aimed at early career professionals working in art therapy who wish to extend their practice and final year students who wish to gain skills and knowledge which could enhance their immediate employment prospects.','The one day workshop explores how to sell art therapy services to schools and CAMHS. Subjects tackled include how to present what you do, promoting your services, tips and approaches to working within an educational culture and transferring your skills into other areas of practice in varied settings.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/setting-up-and-marketing-arts-therapies-in-schools-and-camhs-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530163053','',''),(142,6,'Simple Graphic Design for Businesses - Summer Course','simple-graphic-design-for-businesses-summer-course','','In a crowded and competitive marketplace, developing and maintaining a strong and visible presence is essential for any business. Large or small, established or start-up, all businesses rely on their ability to effectively communicate their services and values to potential customers. That\'s where your \'brand\' comes in.','This course is ideal for SME owners, employees in marketing roles, business start-ups, entrepreneurs and self-employed individuals looking to enhance their visual presence and reputation in their industry and amongst their potential client-base. This would also suit those who wish to gain a broad knowledge of Adobe CS5 Design Standard software.','This 4-day short course has been developed to help small businesses take on the first steps towards their own design. You will be introduced to industry-standard software Adobe Creative Suite CS5, specifically Photoshop, InDesign and Illustrator which will help you to start the design process of your own stationery and logo. The course is strongly focussed on design and production of core promotional materials, beginning with your logo and visual style.\r\n\r\nEach session will start with a short lecture informing the following practical workshop. You will explore how to:\r\n\r\nDevelop a brand identity (sometimes referred to as a corporate or visual identity)\r\n\r\nSuccessfully communicate and visualise your brand values\r\n\r\nUtilise Adobe Creative Suite to artwork, tweak and finalise your designs\r\n\r\nPrepare your designs for print or online applications\r\n\r\nDesign and artwork your own business cards, letterheads and basic marketing materials','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/simple-graphic-design-for-businesses-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530163249','',''),(143,6,'Specialist Dark Room Printing - Black & White Processing - Master Class - Summer Course','specialist-dark-room-printing-black-and-white-processing-master-class-summer-course','','To introduce you to a range of printing techniques other than the traditional black & white printed image using both fibre and acrylic based papers. The course will also include lith printing and lith re-development.','Anyone who has a basic understanding of the dark room and would like to develop their skills or extend their portfolio.','To introduce you to a range of printing techniques other than the traditional black & white printed image. This course builds upon skills learned in the taster course.\r\n\r\nIn this course you will cover different styles of printing including Cyantype, salt and the traditional black & white.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/specialist-dark-room-printing-black-and-white-processing-master-class-summer-course_fees.cfm','course_image20120530163519','',''),(144,6,'Stained Glass for Beginners - Summer Course','stained-glass-for-beginners-summer-course','','To introduce students to the skills they will need to make a leaded stained glass window. Each student should complete a panel of their own design approximately forty centimetres square. Having acquired good basic skills, students may progress at their own speed with individual tutorial support.','Suitable for beginners and those with some prior experience.','Stained glass is a complex art form requiring considerable technical and artistic skill. Having said that, as a beginner it is quite possible to create something beautiful and original given the right support. This course aims to give students a sound technical grounding and an appreciation of this fabulous medium.\r\n\r\nElements of design necessary for working with glass.\r\n\r\nAn introduction to the materials used, choice of glass and information about suppliers.\r\n\r\nNB for the purpose of this course, students will be able to buy all necessary materials from the tutor. Depending upon your design this will cost no more than £80.\r\n\r\nA step by step guide through the various techniques required; preparing a ‘cutline’, cutting glass, leading, soldering and cementing.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/stained-glass-for-beginners-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530163811','',''),(145,6,'Three Media Interactive Workshops - Summer Course','three-media-interactive-workshops-summer-course','','This workshop is aimed at students who wish to develop their creativity further and to learn how to express themselves in different media and methods, as the week progresses. Ideas will be developed from the life model provided.\r\n\r\nThe three medias are Drawing & Painting, Printmaking and Sculpture.','For students with some knowledge and wishing to expand their skill base. Beginners are also welcome.','For the first session you will be guided in the use of various 2D media such as drawing, painting andcollage. You will then move on to interpreting from the same model/pose via the printmaking department where you will learn how to develop an image, based on your earlier sketches, but using printmaking techniques. The third session will be in3 dimensional forms, you will be shown several techniques, such as clay modelling and construction.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/three-media-interactive-workshops-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530164018','',''),(146,6,'Ukulele (for the Complete Beginner) - Summer Course','ukulele-for-the-complete-beginner-summer-course','','Ukuleles are supposed to be the easiest instrument to play (apart from the triangle!!) and once you’ve been shown how to get going I’m sure you will agree. You don’t need to read music, all you need is a ukulele, a slight sense of rhythm and a desire to join in and have fun. A voice is also useful (good, bad or indifferent acceptable) to help keep up the timing and to make things more fun.\r\n\r\nEverything is done within the group, so no solo’s, no intimidation and good fun, with lots of noise and with everyone joining in... You’ll be impressed with how good it will sound.','Suitable for complete beginners with a ukulele.','The course will start with the three basic skills - rhythm, chords (very easy, only 4 strings) and chord changes. You’ll also learn to tune your Uke and have fun with strumming. As the weeks progress you will expand the chords you use which means you’ll be able to learn more tunes to play.\r\n\r\nYou’ll also be given website details of where to obtain ukulele chords and tabs so that you’ll be able to pick out your favorite songs, new and old, to play along with at home.\r\n\r\nA much more pleasant experience by playing in a group environment and lots more fun (the person writing this learned this way and within a few months is playing and performing in a group – so it can be done!)','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/ukulele-for-the-complete-beginner-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530164315','',''),(147,6,'Water Based Ceramic Transfer - Summer Course','water-based-ceramic-transfer-summer-course','','The course introduces students to water based transfers and decals for ceramics. It teaches students how to apply transfers and provides technical teaching on suitable firing programmes for application.','The course is suitable for both complete beginners and for those with previous ceramic experience.','The course is designed for anyone wanting to learn about water based ceramic transfers and their application.\r\n\r\nStudents can bring their own made and glazed ceramic white ware, or purchase blank but glazed ceramic white wear forms for the transfer application techniques.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/water-based-ceramic-transfer-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530164501','',''),(148,6,'Watercolour Painting - Landscapes in Three Days - Summer Course','watercolour-painting-landscapes-in-three-days-summer-course','','This course aims to work on one painting over a period of three days to produce a finished article.','Ideal for beginners or those with basic experience. Great as a gift for someone you know is interested in learning to paint.','This three day course looks at a new aspect each day and includes the following;\r\n\r\nMaterials, your surface and paints\r\n\r\nExamining the landscape\r\n\r\nColour and expression\r\n\r\nMarking out the landscape\r\n\r\nBuilding up layers and working light on dark\r\n\r\nStructures and details\r\n\r\nThis course is for beginners or those with some basic experience and even if you have never picked up a brush then don\'t worry, give it a go! By the end of the course you will have a complete landscape that demonstrates a series of techniques and one which you will want to frame and treasure.','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/watercolour-painting-landscapes-in-three-days-summer-course_details.cfm','course_image20120530164638','',''),(149,6,'Watercolour Painting for Beginners - Summer Course','watercolour-painting-for-beginners-summer-course','','This course aims to develop your understanding of watercolour materials, techniques and to produce a series of paintings.','Ideal for beginners but would help art students past and present to increase portfolios and experience a new medium.','This eight week course will introduce you to Watercolour painting. Each session will deal with some theory and discussion but will largely involve you putting paint on paper and the experience of using paint. We will be working from the landscape as well as still life and our memories. You will also take away with you a series of techniques which will be the foundation to developing more advanced skills.\r\n\r\nThe course will cover;\r\n\r\nMaterials, surface and colour theory\r\n\r\nMixing paint, thickness and skies\r\n\r\nColour and expression\r\n\r\nMarking out and landscapes\r\n\r\nDetail and observation\r\n\r\nTownscapes and buildings\r\n\r\nContemporary approach\r\n\r\nThis course is for beginners and even if you have never picked up a brush then don\'t worry, give it a go! By the end of the course you will have a series of paintings some traditional and others more experimental!','http://www.herts.ac.uk/courses/Watercolour-Painting-for-Beginners--Summer-Course_details.cfm','course_image20120530164837','','');
